# Silicon Labs Project Configuration Tools: slcp, v0, Component selection file.
project_name: zwave_soc_keypad
label: zwave_soc_keypad
description: |
  The Z-Wave certified Door Lock application shows a lock implementation. It will support user codes to open a door and thereby eliminate the need for traditional keys. It is possible to both lock and unlock the door remotely through the Z-Wave protocol.
  For certain devices, the application supports and uses the User Credential Command Class. See README file for details.
category: Z-Wave|Apps
filter:
- name: Device Type
  value:
  - SoC
- name: Project Difficulty
  value:
  - Advanced
- name: Wireless Technology
  value:
  - Z-Wave
package: zwave_sample_app
quality: production
readme:
- path: README.md
source:
- path: app.c
- path: app_cc_event_handlers.c
- path: app_cli.c
- path: app_btn_handler.c
- path: app_cc_door_lock_callbacks.c
tag:
- prebuilt_demo
- toolchain:gcc
- hwfilter:device:device_supports_zwave
include:
- path: .
  file_list:
  - path: app_credentials.h
  - path: events.h
sdk:
  vendor: silabs
  id: simplicity_sdk
  version: 2025.12.1
